Probably one of the better tasting Chinese food in Brooklyn I've had so far. I've been here 3 times and I can say that their food is good. Their lunch options is worth trying, they have vegetables and tofu or vegetable noodles (lo mein or chow mein) with fried yellow rice and onions. I tried their vegetable soup as well, the vegetables were crisp. The staff is nice always pleasant and the food isn't bad. Bring cash--it's cash only. It's not a bad find in an avenue filled with restaurants. There's always other cuisines along this avenue, but if youre on a quick lunch break and you want something fast for cheap, this place isn't a bad option.
